<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98326369547386></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98326369547386><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=4955&mid=98326369547386>Each named Dragon in WW has a chance of dropping a Talisman.</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=4955&mid=98326369547386#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Feb 27th 3:48 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Each named Dragon in WW has a chance of dropping a Talisman.<br><br>Named dragons are rare. Named dragons take at least 3 groups of 51+ players to kill.  They aren't tough compared to VP dragons (these have AE breath that dispells top-right buff, but no AE fear).  People can just click jboots or goblin effect to soak up the dispell.<br><br>Spells are common drop, dragonhide armor and talismans are somewhat common.<br><br>These are no drop, so the NoS isn't going to go down in value.  1/30 people raiding these Dragons will get one of these and chances are, less than 10/30 have a NoS already and more than 20/30 have a twink.<br><br>NoS is still ultra rare.  Camping Drusella is one thing, getting to her and having enough firepower to kill her is another, and having her drop her ultimate rare drop... This is the reason they trade for Hiero Cloaks+ and even Fungus Tunic straight up (40k on Innoruuk).<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
